-- Fortress Investment May Sell Whistler Blackcomb Shares in IPO, Globe Says
-- B y   S e a n   B .   P a s t e r n a k
-- 2010-10-05T11:28:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-05/fortress-investment-may-sell-whistler-blackcomb-shares-in-ipo-globe-says.html
Fortress Investment Group LLC may
sell shares in an initial public offering of Whistler Blackcomb,
a ski venue for the 2010 Winter Olympics, the Globe and Mail
reported, citing unidentified people.  The New York-based investment firm has hired bankers to
explore options for the Canadian resort north of Vancouver, the
 newspaper  said. A filing with regulators ahead of a share sale
is expected soon, the Globe said.  Fortress may also sell the resort, although potential
buyers including businessman  Murray Edwards  and the Ontario
Teachersâ€™ Pension Plan have already passed on the opportunity,
the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
